<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Chen's blog (Posts about cpan)</title><link>http://blog.binchen.org/</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://blog.binchen.org/categories/cpan.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 12 Sep 2020 03:03:00 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Convert TEX to PDF</title><link>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/convert-tex-to-pdf/</link><dc:creator>Chen Bin</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
Install &lt;a href="http://www.tug.org/texlive/"&gt;TexLive&lt;/a&gt; in your OS.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Install &lt;code&gt;latex2pdf&lt;/code&gt; which is dependent on TexLive.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-sh"&gt;cpan App::cpanminus # handy tool to install cpan module
cpanm Template # Template is missing on cygwin
cpanm latex2pdf # finally
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Convert now!
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-sh"&gt;pdf2latex cv.tex
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>cpan</category><category>en</category><category>latex</category><category>pdf</category><category>perl</category><guid>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/convert-tex-to-pdf/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 17 Jul 2012 23:22:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Install perl module through source package on cygwin by using cpanm</title><link>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/install-perl-module-through-source-package-on-cygwin-by-using-cpanm/</link><dc:creator>Chen Bin</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
I failed to install package "Template" by running `cpanm Template'.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
It's because the binary package requires gcc4 while on my cygwin only gcc3 available.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
So I install it from source package (with some hack, of course),
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-sh"&gt;cpanm --look Template # Download and unpack the distribution and then open the directory with your shellI
cpanm . #install from local directory
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Updated: The simpler solution is to install gcc4 at cygwin.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>cpan</category><category>cpanm</category><category>en</category><category>install</category><category>module</category><category>perl</category><guid>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/install-perl-module-through-source-package-on-cygwin-by-using-cpanm/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 17 Jul 2012 23:22:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>